<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005-05-25</DATELINE><TITLE>Global task force for influenza</TITLE><BODY>Early detection and rapid response to bird flu, on a global scale, will drastically cut the costs of dealing with a full-blown human flu pandemic, argue Ron Fouchier, Thijs Kuiken, Guus Rimmelzwaan and Albert Osterhaus.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>